    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Memphis, Tenn.</placeName>
                <date>September 30 1863</date>.</p>
            <p>To the <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Pa</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir! Your favor came duly to hand and the<lb/> contents were duly noted, I am
                already busy<lb/> to re-write the manuscript and will after I have<lb/> done forward
                it to you, I intend, if you think<lb/> proper, to publish a list in the back part of
                the book<lb/> of those who will subscribe for the work especially here in<lb/>
                <placeName>Memphis</placeName>, where I am sanguine that I will be<lb/> able to
                defray the <sic>expences</sic> by their liberal subscription,<lb/> perhaps you will
                be able to do the same in some<lb/> degree, by calling attention to it in the
                Occident,<lb/> the first part containing 8 chapters; do you<lb/> think first to
                re-write it all, or to send it<lb/> as I am going along, it will take me 3 or 4<lb/>
                weeks before I will be able to finish it.</p>
            <p>I believe I do owe you for 2 <add>Hebrew</add> for which<lb/> I will send you the
                money by the by.</p>
            <p>The members of our <add>Hebrew</add> want me to accept the office<lb/> of
                    <add>Hebrew</add>
                <add>?</add> I do not know <sic>If</sic> I shall comply,<lb/> the <persName>Revd
                    Joel Alexander</persName> has given entire satisfactory<lb/> during the
                    <add>Hebrew</add> especially his sermons, as<lb/> I understood from reliable
                parties <persName>Dr S. Turka</persName><lb/> is not so much of
                    <persName>Wise's</persName> school, he is, they<lb/> say, more orthodox, and
                does not advocate,<lb/> reforms, so mote is he!</p>
            <p>With the manuscript I will try to send at<lb/> least $200.00 which will enable you to
                commence<lb/> the work, those who subscribe will have to pay<lb/> in advance, I will
                write you shortly again</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Jacob J Peres</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
